You can get the offset of a timezone using [`ZonedDateTime#getOffset`][1].

Note that the offset of a timezone that observes [DST][2] changes as per the changes in DST. For other places (e.g. India), it remains fixed. Therefore, it is recommended to mention the moment when the offset of a timezone is shown. A moment is mentioned as `Instant.now()` and it represents the date-time in UTC (represented by `Z` which stands for Zulu and specifies the timezone offset of `+00:00` hours).

**Display offset of all timezones returned by `ZoneId.getAvailableZoneIds()`:**

