  [2]: https://stackoverflow.com/a/25001911/56285

[@Jonic&#39;s answer][1] helped me, however I would add a `try { } finally { }` and call `turnOnImplicitWaits()` in the `finally` block to make sure it always turns back on.

    protected boolean isElementHiddenNow(String id) {
        turnOffImplicitWaits();
        boolean result = false;
        try {
           result = ExpectedConditions.invisibilityOfElementLocated(By.id(id)).apply(driver);
        }
        finally {
           turnOnImplicitWaits();
        }
        return result;
    }


